703846f.title: Brooklyn: Court Street - Livingston Street
703846f.text:
Court Street, west side, at Livingston Street, showing in the
foreground at the N.W. corner an excavation conducted by Albert A.
Volk Company. On this site is to be erected the Chamber of Commerce
Building. This is a set of two, consisting of a positive and negative
view.
October 12, 1926.
Albert A. Volk Company.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.
703846f.folder: Court Street & Livingston Street, Brooklyn, NY

703847f-a.title: Brooklyn: Court Street - Livingston Street
703847f-a.text:
78 Court Street, at the S.W. corner of Livingston Street. In this
corner building, was housed the First High School of Brooklyn.
June 11, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
703847f-a.folder: Court Street & Livingston Street, Brooklyn, NY

705479f.title: Brooklyn: Livingston Street - Court Street
705479f.text:
Livingston Street, at and adjoining the N.W. corner of Court
Street, showing partial demolition carried on by Albert A. Volk and
Company. The Chamber of Commerce Building now (1937) occupies the
site. In the right background is seen a section of the Municipal
Building. Note the 4-story building (No. 67) still stands. At the
left, partially seen, is the 6-story Livingston Court Building. This
set consists of a negative and positive view.
June 25, 1926.
Gift of Albert A. Volk Company.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.

703845f.title: Brooklyn: Court Street - Livingston Street
703845f.text:
Court Street (backgground), at Livingston Street, showing an excavation
for the Chamber of Commerce Building at the N.W. corner (foreground).
Also shown are the N.E. and S.E. corners. This is a set of two, showing
the positive and negative views.
October 12, 1924.
Albert A. Volk Company.
